===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1900|1900]], from {{G.}} [[Menarche]] ([[w:1895|1895]]), formed from Greek [[μηνη]] ‘moon’, (on the model of post-classical Latin menorrhagia) + Greek [[αρχη]] ‘beginning’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /mɛ'nɑ:ki/

===Noun===
'''menarche'''
#The onset of [[menstruation]]; the beginning of the [[menstrual]] [[period]]
#:*'''1973''': How old is she?  Nine?  Ten?  The '''menarche''' is not far off – a hint of a bosom, poor child. — Patrick O'Brian, ''HMS Surprise''

